## **CONSOLIDATED INCIDENT COMMANDER SUMMARY** (Post-Quake 06:42 | Status Report
07:25)

**Four incidents surveyed and triaged.** **INC-002 (North Warehouse fire) 
escalated to hazmat coordinator** — chemical identification and evacuation 
radius determination are the blocking decision for neighboring Riverside Tower 
(INC-001). **2 rescue_team + 2 medic_unit units dispatched to Riverside Tower** 
north stairwell to begin extrication of 30+ trapped residents; structural 
assessment confirmed north stairwell usable, south stairwell unsafe. **Metro 
Overpass (INC-003)** assessed as medium priority — concrete spalling confirmed, 
rail service suspended pending engineer sign-off; no immediate life-safety risk.
**Harbor Terminal (INC-004)** remains low priority; commercial inspection 
ongoing.

**Critical blocking decision:** Warehouse manifest retrieval and external agency
chemical identification are required before Riverside Tower evacuation routing 
can be finalized. Hazmat coordinator is standing by for EPA/County Hazmat 
consultation; I have issued mutual-aid escalation requesting expedited manifest 
recovery and chlorine-family oxidizer confirmation.

**Rescue operations at Riverside Tower proceeding independently** — we are 
extracting trapped residents via the structurally sound north stairwell while 
hazmat assessment runs in parallel. Once chemical ID and clearance radius are 
confirmed, logistics will issue evacuation orders for the surrounding area.

**Consolidated SITREP filed** (`sitrep-post-quake-0725.md`) for multi-agency 
distribution. Incident commander awaiting hazmat coordinator's external 
consultation clearance before final evacuation directive.
